Thamsanqa Sangweni penned a permanent deal with the KwaZulu-Natal-based Premier Soccer League club. CAPE TOWN - Maritzburg United have confirmed the signing of former Mamelodi Sundowns and Orlando Pirates defensive midfielder Thamsanqa Sangweni. Sangweni penned a permanent deal with the KwaZulu-Natal-based Premier Soccer League club. The 30-year-old played six matches for Richards Bay in the National First Division last season. In 2017, Sangweni moved from Chippa United to Orlando Pirates on a two-year deal, following in his brother's footsteps who had played there for five years. 